# STATEMENT OF WORK (SOW)

## Livelihood Security Platform — Desktop Admin Application (POC)

---

## 1. Parties

**Client:**
Livelihood Security Platform (or Client Organization)

**Service Provider:**
[Engineering Partner / Internal Product Team]

**Engagement Type:**
Fixed-scope Proof of Concept (POC)

---

## 2. Background & Context

The Client is conducting a **Proof of Concept** to validate the operational feasibility of a **desktop-first administrative system** that enables institutions to:

* Manage informal workers
* Assign jobs
* Enforce minimum income guarantees
* Execute payments
* Maintain auditable work histories

This SOW defines the **scope, deliverables, timelines, and responsibilities** for building this POC.

---

## 3. Objectives

### Primary Objective

Deliver a **working desktop (Electron) POC** that enables ops teams to complete a **full livelihood cycle**:

> Worker → Job → Income Guarantee → Payment → Ledger

### Secondary Objectives

* Demonstrate income stabilization logic
* Prove payment reliability
* Establish auditability
* Support pilot evaluation by institutions

---

## 4. Scope of Work

### 4.1 In-Scope Deliverables

#### A. Desktop Application (Electron)

* Cross-platform desktop app (Windows priority)
* Fixed sidebar + sticky top bar layout
* Keyboard-usable interface
* High data-density tables

#### B. Core Functional Modules

1. Dashboard (read-only overview)
2. Worker Registry
3. Job Management
4. Income Guarantee Rules
5. Payments Execution
6. Work History (Immutable Ledger)
7. Reports (CSV export)
8. Settings (basic configuration)

#### C. Backend Services

* REST APIs
* Authentication (admin/ops roles)
* Business rules engine (income guarantee)
* Payment trigger service
* Audit logging

#### D. Data Storage

* Backend persistence (cloud or local)
* Local desktop cache (SQLite)
* Immutable ledger model

---

### 4.2 Explicitly Out of Scope

* Worker-facing mobile or web apps
* Insurance automation
* Credit scoring or lending
* Advanced analytics / AI
* Branding or visual design polish
* Production-grade scalability

---

## 5. Functional Requirements Summary

| Area             | Requirement                       |
| ---------------- | --------------------------------- |
| Workers          | Create, edit, activate/deactivate |
| Jobs             | Create, assign, close             |
| Income Guarantee | Calculate and apply top-ups       |
| Payments         | Trigger, track, retry             |
| Ledger           | Append-only, immutable            |
| Reports          | Exportable summaries              |

(Full detail governed by the approved PRD & Tech Specs)

